        description:
            "Do you want to live the experience of a Multinational with the dynamism of a Startup?\n\nIf you are looking for an internship that will test your skills and boost your career, our Schneider Trainee Program is for you.\n\nBe part of an inclusive environment in which for 6 months you can co-create solutions to key challenges in the industry learning from our experts.\n\nTake your creativity and innovation to another level while enjoying a paid internship with flexible hours and interactive workshops.\n\nJoin our #SEGreatPeople\n\nüè¢Departament and Project description:\n\nOur department is on a mission to empower Schneider Electric's business in Iberia, supporting over 4,000 users. We focus on delivering exceptional service and driving innovative projects in key areas like Networking, Infrastructure, and Artificial Intelligence.\n\nBe part of a team that shapes the future of technology, ensuring seamless operations and transformative solutions for our users.\n\nüöÄ What will you learn?\n\n* Manage incidents and technical support with the Service Desk and various internal clients.\n* Understand the main IT support tools, infrastructure solutions (both On-Prem and Cloud), as well as the network infrastructure of the various offices in Spain and Portugal.\n* Learn about the Infrastructure, Network, and Artificial Intelligence systems we use at Schneider Electric.\n* Collaborate in the adoption of new solutions and technologies, with the goal of digital transformation.\n* Assist in managing demands and support in the areas of Infrastructure, Network, and Artificial Intelligence.\n* Collaborate in the implementation and monitoring of action plans to improve the use of digital tools by users.\n* Contribute to the creation of action plans to promote Green IT and improve the sustainability of existing infrastructure.\n* Be part of the Talent Discovery for Iberian IT Hub program, with the possibility of permanent incorporation in the IT Digital area.\n\nüîç Are you who we are looking for?\n\n* Undergraduate or master's student in Telecommunications Engineering, Computer Engineering, or similar with a passion for technology.\n* Technical knowledge in infrastructure, networks, or Artificial Intelligence is valued.\n* Interest or knowledge in business and management areas is valued.\n* Good communication skills and eagerness to learn.\n* Advanced knowledge of Excel and the rest of the Office365 package.\n* Analytical skills.\n* Proactive and with a growth mindset\n* Fluent in English, both written and verbally as you will be part of a global team\n* To be able to work between 4 and 6 hours a day (Monday to Friday).\n* To be able to make an internship agreement with your university or study center for a period of at least 6 months.\n\nWhat can we offer?\n\nüéØ An experience specially designed for your learning and development\n\nüíµ Paid internships (depending on the schedule you establish, min. 20 hours and max. 30 hours per week, 700-900 euros / month)\n\nü§© Track your evolution and learning\n\n‚åö Time flexibility to combine it with your studies\n\nüßò‚ÄçOne day of free disposal per month (cumulative)\n\nüíª Possibility to collaborate remotely depending on the position (up to 2 days per week).\n\nüôå Duration of 6 months with the possibility of extension or contracting\n\n*We seek out and reward people for putting the customer first, being disruptive to the status quo, embracing different perspectives, continuously learning, and acting like owners. We want our employees to reflect the diversity of the communities in which we operate. We welcome people as they are, creating an inclusive culture where all forms of diversity are seen as a real value for the company. We‚Äôre looking for people with a passion for success ‚Äî on the job and beyond.",
